[35m│[0m was found in HAProxy before 2.0.6. In legacy mode, messages featuring a      [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m transfer-encoding header missing the &quot;chunked&quot; value were not      [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m being correctly rejected. The impact was limited but if combined with the    [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m &quot;http-reuse always&quot; setting, it could be used to help construct an [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m HTTP request smuggling attack against a vulnerable component employing a     [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m lenient parser that would ignore the content-length header as soon as it saw [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m a transfer-encoding one (even if not entirely valid according to the         [35m│[0m
