[32m╭─[0m[32m───────────────────────────────[0m[32m [0m[1;32mLLM Response[0m[32m [0m[32m───────────────────────────────[0m[32m─╮[0m
[32m│[0m ## Research Summary: HAProxy 2.0.5 HTTP Request Smuggling Vulnerabilities    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### detailed_summary                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Successfully researched known HTTP Request Smuggling vulnerabilities in      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m HAProxy 2.0.5 using curl to access online CVE databases. Accessed NIST NVD   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (National Vulnerability Database) and retrieved detailed information for     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m both target CVEs. Exploit-db is accessible online but requires               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m authentication for detailed exploit searches. No local exploit database      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m tools (searchsploit) were available in the container.                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **CVE-2019-18277**: Confirmed HTTP Request Smuggling vulnerability affecting [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m HAProxy versions before 2.0.6, which includes version 2.0.5. This is a CL.TE [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (Content-Length vs Transfer-Encoding) smuggling variant that occurs in       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m legacy mode when combined with "http-reuse always" setting.                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **CVE-2020-11100**: Confirmed CRITICAL HTTP/2 HPACK buffer overflow          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m vulnerability affecting HAProxy 1.8 through 2.x before 2.1.4, which includes [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m version 2.0.5. This vulnerability allows remote code execution through       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m crafted HTTP/2 requests.                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### proofs                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **CVE-2019-18277 Details (from NVD):**                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m A flaw was found in HAProxy before 2.0.6. In legacy mode, messages featuring [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m a transfer-encoding header missing the "chunked" value were not being        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m correctly rejected. The impact was limited but if combined with the          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "http-reuse always" setting, it could be used to help construct an HTTP      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m request smuggling attack against a vulnerable component employing a lenient  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m parser that would ignore the content-length header as soon as it saw a       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m transfer-encoding one (even if not entirely valid according to the           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m specification).                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **CVE-2020-11100 Details (from NVD):**                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m In hpack_dht_insert in hpack-tbl.c in the HPACK decoder in HAProxy 1.8       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m through 2.x before 2.1.4, a remote attacker can write arbitrary bytes around [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m a certain location on the heap via a crafted HTTP/2 request, possibly        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m causing remote code execution.                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Version Confirmation:**                                                    [32m│[0m
